description.narrative: Efforts in 2019 focused on (i) monitoring progress on KRC#8, technical guidance to improve the effectiveness and sustainability of programmes, and increasing political prioritization for sanitation, (ii) further actions towards the new Strategic Plan (SP) and SDG agendas [Urban WASH, Climate Resilient WASH, Disaster Risk Reduction and WASH in Institutions] and (iii) continued strengthening emergency WASH preparedness, response and sector coordination, including cholera/Ebola (DRC, Central Sahel, Cameroon, CAR). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019

title.narrative: (4-TA/ WASH in Schools) # of countries which have integrated SDG 6.1 and 6.2 indicators into national level monitoring systems for Education (EMIS)
(2- Sanitation & Ending Open Defecation) Number of countries with a costed plan to end open defecation
(5-Resilient WASH Services- Climate and Public Health Risks) Number of countries integrated climate change and risk management (including cholera) into WASH sector plan
(6- TA Adolescent Girls) # of countries that have incorporated menstrual hygiene management standards and targets into national WASH in schools strategies (proposed SP indicator)
(7- Evidence/ Knowledge Management) Number of knowledge product developed in countries in the region with support from the Regional Office
(1-Partnerships) # of key global and regional WASH initiatives in which UNICEF is the co-chair or provides coordination support (same as 2016-2017, SP 2014-17 P3.f.2)
(3- Safe & Sustainable Water Supply Services) Number of countries implementing independent sustainabiliy checks with a clear feedback mechanism
(8-Oversight/ WiE Quality) % of countries in Humanitarian action with WASH coordination mechanisms meeting CCC standards (proposed SP Result 4.1 indicator)
